[SN]TITLE[SN]
Exeter woman Christine Copley who starved son jailed

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A mother who starved her son, leaving him to eat hamster food and dog biscuits, has been jailed for three years.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Christine Copley, 66, ill treated her son Andrew, now 39, for more than 10 years, a court heard.
His Christmas presents were sold at car boot sales and a neighbour who saw bruising on his body called him "the saddest little boy I ever saw".
Copley, of Laburnum Road, Exeter, was found guilty of six counts of cruelty.
